review_blob: Has a nutty, chocolate aroma, and near black color.  Medium body and full flavor.  Great drinkability. A standard for porters.
Dark brown color with minimal head. Coffee and chocolate aroma. Same for the flavor. A little more bitter than I expected. Nice nutty finish.
Nice cloudy golden color with a thick head.  Good yeasty aroma.  Sublte taste of banana and clove.  Was expecting a stronger flavor.  Still a good hefe.
Cloudy auburn with a thick head.  Nice yeasty aroma.  Lots of flavor with a sweet and nutty banana taste.  Very enjoyable.
Deep golden color, nice floral and citrusy aroma.  Big hops flavor, but a good maltiness to back it up.  Long bitter finish.  Very good.
Pours a deep red with minimal head. Holiday spice aroma, and can taste the carmel malts with spices.  Very good.
Nutty and slightly sweet aroma. Clear mahogany color with nice head.  Balanced taste, not too sweet. Toffee flavors. Very drinkable. Recommend it.

Nice robust aroma of dark chocolate and boozy molasses.  Pours pitch black with a dark brown head.  Molasses taste to start with a bitter finish, coffee and dark chocolate notes as well.  Full thick body with a long finish.  Definitely a sipping beer. Awesome stout.

Mahogony color with a thick head and good retention. Cant pinpoint the aroma. Medium sourness for taste and a bit thin on the palate.  Overall, not my style of beer.  Would suit pairing with a meal instead of drinking on its own.
Nice citrusy aroma. Medium bitterness with a nice finish.  Very good pale ale....er lager.  Probably best Sam Adams hoppy beer.
Deep caramel color with a cream colored head. Sweet aroma and taste with a nice bourbon flavor coming through.  Excellent beer.
beer_name: Brau Brothers Barrel Aged Belgian Style Quad

review_blob: Aroma of caramel, vanilla. Pours a nice red color with good clarity and a small white head.  Medium bitterness and sweetness with a medium body, but somehow does not seem balanced.  The finish is overpowered by an alcohol flavor.  Letting it warm up to room temp seemed to help bring out the caramel malt flavors and tastes better.
beer_name: Madhouse Venture Series Oak Aged Imperial Red
